nodes.text: Lin-Manuel Miranda is an American composer, actor, playwright and rapper best known for creating the Broadway musicals In the Heights and Hamilton. With director J.J. Abrams, he composed two tracks for Star Wars Episode VII The Force Awakens entitled "Jabba Flow" and "Dobra Doompa". He and Abrams sang the vocals. He also had a cameo as a Resistance pilot for the victory celebration on Ajan Kloss in Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker.
